    "When correlating semantic similarity with reappraisal quality, we found that similarity to vignette was consistently related to better reappraisal quality over all four indicators for both GPT and humans, but only in Studies 1 and 2 (Table 2).",
    "In Study 4, which involved a diverse range of user-submitted vignettes instead of a set of researcher-provided vignettes, only reappraisal effectiveness within the human condition was positively associated with semantic similarity to vignette.",
    "Correlations between similarity of reappraisal to vignette and all four quality dimensions for humans and GPT.",
    "Correlations are displayed separately for study 1 (left in cell), study 2 (middle in cell), and study 4 (right in cell).",
    "* p <.05, ** p <.01, *** p <.001."
